549	+//! Kernel-call dispatch — the `SYSTEM` task's role.
550	+//!
551	+//! In MINIX 3, `SYSTEM` is a kernel pseudo-task: it has a proc-table slot but
552	+//! no scheduler context. When a server `SENDREC`s the `SYSTEM` endpoint, the
553	+//! IPC fast path in `proc.c::do_ipc` short-circuits into `kernel_call()`
554	+//! (`kernel/system.c`), which runs synchronously in the *caller's* EL1 stack
555	+//! and writes the reply back into the caller's user buffer. The caller never
556	+//! actually blocks on a receiver; SYSTEM's `IMAGE` entry exists only so that
557	+//! the endpoint encodes to a valid `ProcNr`.
558	+//!
559	+//! MINIX 4 inherits exactly that shape. [`ipc::dispatch`] detects
560	+//! `src_dst_e == boot_endpoint(SYSTEM)` in the SENDREC arm and diverts here
561	+//! instead of calling [`ipc::send::mini_send`]; the rest of the IPC engine is
562	+//! untouched.
563	+//!
564	+//! [`ipc::dispatch`]: crate::ipc
565	+//! [`ipc::send::mini_send`]: crate::ipc
566	+
567	+mod do_getinfo;
568	+mod stubs;
