1	//! IPC subsystem — the heart of the MINIX microkernel.
2	//!
3	//! Slice 2.5 lights up the real IPC engine. `do_ipc` is the single SVC
4	//! entry point; it materializes mutable borrows of `PROC_TABLE` and
5	//! `PRIV_TABLE`, performs trap-mask gating, and dispatches to one of the
6	//! per-primitive handlers (`mini_send`, `mini_receive`, `mini_notify`,
7	//! `mini_senda`). The handlers operate on the explicit table slices —
8	//! they never touch the static directly — which keeps each primitive
9	//! testable in isolation and prevents the two-`&mut`-from-one-
10	//! `UnsafeCell` UB hazard that arises if each primitive re-borrows
11	//! individual slots.
12	//!
13	//! After every SVC, `el1_svc_tail` runs `schedule_next` to pick the
14	//! highest-priority runnable proc and flush any pending `MF_DELIVERMSG`
15	//! into its user buffer. That keeps the run queue honest when the caller
16	//! blocks (`rts_set` already dequeued it) and ensures a receiver that
17	//! got unblocked sees its message before resuming.
